# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Simply use brute force and one thing here is that length of any integer can't be more than three because 255 is limit so we can use 4 loops of 3 size and check if individual integers are less than 256 .
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Use 4 loops from 1 to 3 and check the substrings are less than 256 .
Some Implementation Techniques to be taken care of:
- first check i+j+k+m== s.size because we should not take some part of string that is valid but not of given string size.
- then don't take directly substr because it can have leading zeroes like "`255 045 003 12`" On taking stoi leading zeores will be gone then convert to string again.(Beacuse (str)"045"--> (int)$$45$$)
- then compare with 256 to all substrings use stoi again  for comparing .(Direct string comparison may not work)
- then add the dots in btween substrings and check if final length is given string length + 3 then push in ans (in case if it exceeds size or less than so make sure to check).
- **HelpFull?UpVoTe🔼:❤**
# Complexity
- Time complexity:($$O(1)$$) Actually $$O(M^N*N)$$
- Since loops $$O(M*M*M*M)$$  and then substr take another N iterations.
- Here M=3 and N=4 so constant time
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(1)$$
- actually $$O(N*M)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

