# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
try out all possibilities. 
first possibility: take single character
second and thirs possibility: take 2 and 3 characters respectively. for this case ensure that number doesn't start with 0 and is less than 255
count number of dots you add (i.e splits you have made). if this is equal to 3 (excluding last dot added ) and end of string is reached we have a valid ip
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
we can use dfs to explore all the combinations. 
at each ith postion, we need to try out with next i +1, i+2 and i+3 substring. 
if this substring is valid (for single digit 0-9 are valid cases and for 2 or 3 digits if them number doesn't start with 0 and is less than 255) proceed for next 1 to 3 substr
we stop only when 

