# Intuition
We will consider every 1 ,2 and 3 size substrings and try to partition the string into 4 parts and see if they match our condition. We will make use of recursion(backtracking) in it.

# Approach
We will consider every 1,2 and 3 size substrings with conditions-
- The total partitions should be 4
- We should not have any preceding 0.
- If we reach the end we will add the string to our ans

So at every ind, we have 3 cases. 
- We will add the single char to our ans string and add "." at end
- We will add the next 2 characters and add "." at end. Here we have to check whether it is valid or not(first char should not be 0).
- We will add the next 3 characters and add "." at end. Here we have to check whether it is valid or not(first char should not be 0) along with that it should not be greater that 255.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
We are making 3 recursion calls at every index. SO TC (3^n).

- Space complexity:
SC O(n^2)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    bool isValid(string s)
    {
        if(s[0]=='0')
            return false;
        int n=stoi(s);
        if(n<=255)return true;
        return false;
    }

    void helper(int ind,int part,int n,string &s,string ans,vector<string>&res)
    {
        if(ind==n and part==4)
        {
            ans.pop_back(); //To remove that last dot "."
            res.push_back(ans);
        }
        if(ind==n || part==4)return;

        helper(ind+1,part+1,n,s,ans+s[ind]+".",res);
        if(ind+2<=n and isValid(s.substr(ind,2)))
            helper(ind+2,part+1,n,s,ans+s.substr(ind,2)+".",res);
        if(ind+3<=n and isValid(s.substr(ind,3)))
            helper(ind+3,part+1,n,s,ans+s.substr(ind,3)+".",res);
    }
    vector<string> restoreIpAddresses(string s) {
        vector<string>res;
        int n=s.size();
        helper(0,0,n,s,"",res); 
        return res;
    }
};
```

