Exaplanation to Approach :

This is a backtracking problem with a few slightly convoluted conditions.

There needs to be 4 parts per IP. There are always three dots/four candidates (2.5.5.2.5.5.1.1.1.3.5 is not valid, neither is 1.1.1)
1. When selecting a candidate, it can't have more than 3 characters (2552.55.111.35 is not valid)
2. When selecting a candidate, its characters cant be above 255 (25.525.511.135 is not valid because of 525 and 511)
When selecting a candidate
3. IF the candidate has 2 or more characters, then the first can't be a zero.
4.  (1.0.1.023 is not valid as member 023 is size>1 and leads with 0. But 0.0.0.0 is valid as each candidate is size 1)

The main idea to solve this problem is to use Recursion.
Consider every position of the input string and, there exist two possible cases:
Place a dot over the current position.
Take this character, i.e don’t place the dot over this position.
At every step of the recursion, we have the following data:
curr stores the string between two dots.
res stores the possible IP Address.
index stores the current position in the input string.
At each index, first, add the character to curr and check whether the integer that we have is in the range [0,255] then, we can move further otherwise return.
When we reach the end of the input string, we’ll check whether we have a valid IP Address or not, If yes, insert the IP Address into our answer.
