solutions.content:
First we have to Think about the range and Preprocess the data ,
 Suppose If any number in the array is greater than 247 ,then it can never have its 4byte UTF-8

So lets find range ,So if first four bit is set ,then that number must be greater than or equal to 240.
 If first three bits get set ,then that number must be greater than or equal to 224.
If first two bits are set then the number must be greater than or equal to 192.
If first one digit gets set ,then the number must be greater than 128 and these number must get followed by any of the above number ,otherwise we have to return false.
if number is less than 128 ,then it will be 1 byte number.
So ,what we have to do ,if we encounter any number ,first we find range ,and then we take consceutive array elements and check whether it is greater than 128 and less than 192 or not ,if it is then we go in a loop ,otherwise we return false.

```
class Solution {
    public boolean validUtf8(int[] data) {        
        for(int i = 0 ; i < data.length ; i++){
            if(data[i] > 247){
                return false;
            }
            int tillThisIndex = range(data[i]);
            if(tillThisIndex == -1){
                continue;
            }else if(tillThisIndex == 0){
                return false;
            }else if(tillThisIndex > 0){
                i++;
                int h = i+tillThisIndex;
                while(i<data.length && i<h){
                    if(range(data[i]) == 0){
                        i++;
                    }else{
                        return false;
                    }
                }
                if(i < h){
                    return false;
                }
                i--;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }


    public int range(int number){
        if(number >= 240){
            return 3;
        }else if(number >= 224){
            return 2;
        }else if(number >= 192){
            return 1;
        }else if(number >= 128){
            return 0;
        }else{
            return -1;
        }
    }
}
```

